This paper is primarily focused on face recognition, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) category. The paper also proposes a novel graph-structured module and a conditional-margin loss function, which are related to deep learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of different domains such as NIR and sketch also suggests a potential connection to multimedia (cs.MM) and cryptography (cs.CR) sub-categories.
